The paper discusses wireless energy transmission for sensor activation, which falls under the category of networked sensors and wireless sensor networks. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of orthogonal frequencies to avoid destructive interference, which falls under the category of electromagnetic theory and applications, making cs.EM (Electromagnetics) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also discusses the development of low-energy battery-less sensor nodes, which falls under the category of electronic devices and circuits, making cs.ET (Embedded Systems) a possible sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of multiple transmitters to compensate for path-loss attenuation, which falls under the category of control systems and robotics, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of spectrum analysis to measure received power, which falls under the category of information theory and signal processing, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible sub-category.
